<h1 id="introduction">Introduction</h1>

<p><a href="https://jekyllrb.com/">Jekyll</a> is a simple static website generator, with blog knowledge, for personal, project or organization websites. Written in <a href="https://www.ruby-lang.org/">Ruby</a> and created by Tom Preston-Werner, co-founder of <a href="https://github.com/">GitHub</a>, it is distributed under the <a href="https://opensource.org/">open source</a> <a href="https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT">MIT license</a>.</p>

<p>Jekyll is the mechanism behind the pages of GitHub, a feature of GitHub that allows users to host websites based on their GitHub repositories for free.</p>

<!-- QUADRADO -->
<script async="" src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>

